 variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"RENTY","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Jose, Angel, Alicia, Bolivar, Francisco, Jorge, Juan, Julio, Magda, Manuel, Nydia, Virgen.","Spanish and Portuguese: most probably from <i>renta</i> ‘income’, ‘rental’. This name is common mainly in the Caribbean; it is rare in Spain."],"variants":[{"name":"Rentas","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Carlos, Jose, Pedro, Ramonita, Angel, Juan, Manuel, Mario, Tomas, Aida, Armando, Blanca.","Spanish and Portuguese: plural form of   Renta  ."]}]},{"name":"Arnould","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Saxon, Latin: Faithful to his honour; help in war, helping lord; powerful lord."],"variants":[]},{"name":"III","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Japanese Yuko, Aiko, Hideaki, Hiroki, Hiroyuki, Isamu, Kaoru, Katsumi, Keiichiro, Kenji, Masako, Masayuki.","Japanese: variously written, sometimes with characters used phonetically; the most probable meanings are 仁井 ‘benevolent well’, 新居 ‘new residence’, or 新井 ‘new well’. It is not common in Japan."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Arnould III de RENTY was born in 1225, in Renty, Pas-de-Calais, Hauts-de-France, France, his father, Baron Allard ou Alain de Renty, was 34 and his mother, Nicole de Neulles, was 21. He had at least 2 sons and 1 daughter with Marguerite BOUDET de GROVILLE. He died in 1290, in his hometown, at the age of 6